text.tspan: Fish catch per unit of fishing power, England and Wales
Fish catch is measured as the amount of landings – fish brought back to land – of bottom-dwelling fish. This is
given per unit of fishing power: the number of fishing vessels multiplied by the fishing effort per vessel.
Data source: Ruth Thurstan et al. (2010). The effects of 118 years of industrial fishing on UK bottom trawl fisheries. Nature Communications.
